    <!-- About Section from about.ejs -->
    <section id="about" class="section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>About the Event</h2>
            <p>Type Till Sunrise is not just another blogging 
                contest — it’s a creative showdown under the stars that 
                blends the excitement of a hackathon with the flair of 
                creative writing. This unique overnight inter-university 
                blogathon is designed to push your creative limits while 
                testing your speed, adaptability, and teamwork in a 
                high-pressure, high-energy environment. <br> <br>
                Unlike traditional competitions, Type Till Sunrise 
                unfolds over the course of a 12-hour overnight marathon. From 
                sunset to sunrise, teams will work together to brainstorm, draft, 
                refine, and present creative blogs across multiple dynamic rounds. 
                Each round brings new challenges, unexpected twists, and a chance 
                for your team to shine.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Rounds Section from about.ejs -->
    <section id="rounds" class="section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Competition Rounds</h2>
            <div class="rounds-container">
                <div class="round-card-animated">
                    <div class="round-front">
                        <div class="round-icon">
                            <i class="fas fa-pen-fancy"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Round 1: Topic Takedown</h3>
                        <p class="round-brief">Teams will select a predefined topic (first-come, first-served, max 5 teams per topic) 
                            and write a well-structured blog within 2 hours. The blog will be evaluated for relevance (auto-checked), 
                            originality (manual plagiarism check), and content quality. Submissions must be in Word format (.docx).</p>
                        <button class="learn-more-btn">Learn More</button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="round-back">
                        <h4>Topic Takedown Details</h4>
                        <ul class="round-details">
                            <li><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Duration: 2 hours</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-tasks"></i> Word Limit: 800-1000 words</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="round-description">
                            <p>Choose from limited topic slots and create a compelling blog post. Topics will be revealed at the start of the round.</p>
                            <h5>Judging Criteria:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Content Quality (40%)</li>
                                <li>Creativity (30%)</li>
                                <li>Structure (20%)</li>
                                <li>Language (10%)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="round-card-animated">
                    <div class="round-front">
                        <div class="round-icon">
                            <i class="fas fa-headphones"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Round 2: Audible to Article</h3>
                        <p class="round-brief">A typing speed challenge where one team member 
                            transcribes an audio clip in real time. The system will auto-calculate typing speed (WPM) 
                            and accuracy, with deductions for spelling errors. The winner will be announced immediately 
                            and awarded a medal and certificate on the spot.</p>
                        <button class="learn-more-btn">Learn More</button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="round-back">
                        <h4>Audible to Article Details</h4>
                        <ul class="round-details">
                            <li><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Duration: 1 hour</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-keyboard"></i> Min WPM: 40</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="round-description">
                            <p>Listen to audio content and transform it into a well-structured article while maintaining accuracy and adding creative elements.</p>
                            <h5>Judging Criteria:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Accuracy (40%)</li>
                                <li>Formatting (30%)</li>
                                <li>Speed (20%)</li>
                                <li>Enhancement (10%)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="round-card-animated">
                    <div class="round-front">
                        <div class="round-icon">
                            <i class="fas fa-eye-slash"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Round 3: Eyes Shut, Words Flow</h3>
                        <p class="round-brief">One team member dictates, and another blindfolded member types in a live text box. 
                            The system will automatically check spelling accuracy, typing speed, and topic relevance. The most 
                            accurate and fastest team will be declared winners immediately and awarded a medal and certificate.</p>
                        <button class="learn-more-btn">Learn More</button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="round-back">
                        <h4>Eyes Shut, Words Flow Details</h4>
                        <ul class="round-details">
                            <li><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Duration: 1.5 hours</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-users"></i> Team Coordination Required</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="round-description">
                            <p>One team member dictates while another types with eyes closed, testing trust and coordination.</p>
                            <h5>Judging Criteria:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Typing Accuracy (35%)</li>
                                <li>Team Coordination (30%)</li>
                                <li>Content Quality (25%)</li>
                                <li>Time Management (10%)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="round-card-animated">
                    <div class="round-front">
                        <div class="round-icon">
                            <i class="fas fa-crown"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h3>Round 4: The Creator's Arena</h3>
                        <p class="round-brief">Teams will choose their own topic (unique per team) and submit both a blog and 
                            a 2-minute pitch video. The system will auto-check relevance, while judges evaluate content quality 
                            and presentation. </p>
                        <button class="learn-more-btn">Learn More</button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="round-back">
                        <h4>Creator's Arena Details</h4>
                        <ul class="round-details">
                            <li><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Duration: 5 hours total</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Word Limit: 1200 words</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="round-description">
                            <p>Create a comprehensive blog with multimedia elements and present through a pitch video.</p>
                            <h5>Sub-rounds:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Ideation & Writing (3 hours)</li>
                                <li>Visual Enhancement (1 hour)</li>
                                <li>Video Pitch (1 hour)</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h5>Judging Criteria:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Content Quality (30%)</li>
                                <li>Visual Appeal (25%)</li>
                                <li>Presentation (25%)</li>
                                <li>Innovation (20%)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

